<main class="content" id="top">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h1>It's The Snake Game</h1>
    <p class="lede">The classic arcade Snake, rebuilt for the browser. Press space, steer with the arrows, and see how long your snake can grow before it bites its own tail.</p>

    <h2 id="how">How to play</h2>
    <p>Getting going takes one key. When the screen loads you'll see the start prompt — tap the space bar and the snake starts sliding.</p>
    <div class="keys">
      <span class="key">Space — start / pause</span>
      <span class="key">↑ ↓ ← → — steer</span>
      <span class="key">W A S D — also steer</span>
      <span class="key">P — pause</span>
    </div>
    <p>Guide the snake onto the blinking block to eat it. Every block adds <strong>10 points</strong>, grows your snake by one segment, and nudges the speed up a touch. The game ends if you run into a wall or into your own tail — so the longer you get, the more carefully you have to plan your turns.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>On desktop:</strong> arrow keys or WASD.</li>
      <li><strong>On a phone or tablet:</strong> swipe in any direction, or use the on-screen pad below the screen.</li>
      <li><strong>Your best score</strong> is saved on your own device, so you always have a target to beat.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="ad-slot" aria-hidden="true">Advertisement</div>

    <h2>Tips for a higher score</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Think one move ahead.</strong> The snake can't reverse into itself, so decide your next turn before you reach the block, not as you arrive.</li>
      <li><strong>Hug the edges.</strong> Running laps around the outside keeps the middle open and gives you room to react.</li>
      <li><strong>Don't chase every block.</strong> If the food spawns in a tight spot, take the long way round rather than trapping yourself.</li>
      <li><strong>Leave yourself an exit.</strong> As the snake fills the board, always keep a clear path back out of any pocket you enter.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>A quick history of Snake</h2>
    <p>Snake is one of the most-played video game concepts ever made. The idea dates back to the 1976 arcade game <em>Blockade</em>, but it reached hundreds of millions of players when a version shipped preloaded on Nokia mobile phones at the end of the 1990s. Its appeal has always been the same: rules you understand in seconds, and a difficulty curve you create yourself as your snake grows longer.</p>

    <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details><summary>How do I start the game?</summary><p>Press the space bar. The snake begins moving immediately — steer it with the arrow keys.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Do I need to download or sign up for anything?</summary><p>No. The game runs entirely in your browser. There's nothing to install and no account to create.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Can I play Snake on my phone?</summary><p>Yes. Swipe on the game screen to change direction, or tap the on-screen arrow pad that appears on touch devices.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How is my high score saved?</summary><p>It's stored locally in your browser, so it stays on your device. Clearing your browser data will reset it.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Is it really free?</summary><p>Completely free. The site is supported by advertising, which lets the game stay open to everyone.</p></details>
    </div>

    <h2 id="about">About</h2>
    <p>It's The Snake Game is a free, browser-based take on one of the most familiar games ever made — no download, no account, just press space and play. It's built with plain HTML, CSS and JavaScript drawn onto a canvas, which keeps it fast and works across modern browsers without plugins. Your high score is stored locally on your own device, not on a server. The site is free to play and supported by advertising.</p>

